introduction:
A London trained graphic designer with 15 years professional experience in interactive design,advertising, creative direction, branding, film and events.Martin now run's a creative studio, Mountains Of Imagination (MoI) which specializes in presentation consultancy. The studio's work results in delivering visual, emotive and effective story telling documents for small and medium sized business as well as departments and CMO's in the Beijing automotive industry and other multi national company's. The MoI studio’s methodology and processes help guide it's clients to clear messages and bold visuals. As well as working directly with clients on their content, message, design and performance skills MoI has also developed four different workshops to enable inpiduals and teams to have more confidence in presentation spotlight moments where ideas are shared and opportunities created.
1. The 8 Steps to Showtime - preparation road map
2. Lean Presentation Design - all you need to get presenting
3. Get Creative With Your iPad - empower yourself
4. The Elevator Pitch - snappy story telling
He is also the creative director for Wheels Plus Wings an amazing social venture who's aim is to improve mobility for disabled children and so have positive effects for their independent future, their families and communities for which he developed the name, brand identity and design. Martin has also given a TEDxBeijing talk in 2010 where he spoke about a truly innovative project he developed for Peugeot cars where he co-directed a series of short films where blind and visually impaired photographers became sensory art directors and worked on 18mins of branded content split over 8 web films. In 2014/2015 he is also coaching potential next TEDx speakers to help them define their message and organize their ideas.
Martin believes strongly that when we live in such a visual world surrounded by smart phones and tablets our ideas are never out of arms reach and it has now never been easier to share good ideas and get stuff done.
title: Graphic designer
